summary: Crashed in a field while attemptting to land.
George Sherlock was killed when his mail plane crashed into a chimney while attempting to land at Heller Field in poor visibility.

The plane failed to gain altitude after taking off from Criclklewood and crashed into a tree and a house. Pilot error in taking off towards a hill in unfavorable wind conditions and fog.The first commercial air disaster to result in passenger fatalities during a regularly scheduled service..
Crashed while making an approach to Le Bourget Airport in Paris. Pilot aborted the landing due to another aircraft on the runway.
On approach to Geraldton the plane crashed near the Murchinson River. Considered the first commercial flight in Australila.
The plane ditched into the ocean about 40 miles East of Florida after a propeller blade broke. Only the pilot survived, being picked up over 2 days later. The flying boat was named Miss Miami.

A midair collision occurred at 400 ft. in poor visibility approximately 18 miles north of Beauvais, France. The pilots of both planes were using the road as a route marker in bad weather and poor visibility. This was the  first commercial midair collision in aviation history. Two killed on the de Havilland, five on the Faman F-60.
Went down into the English Channel while en route.

The passenger/mail plane lost it's engine while taking off and crashed into trees. Actress Fern Andra survived the accident but her director, Georg Bluen did not. The pilot, Lothar von Richthofen, was also killed. He was a World War I ace and brother of Manfred von Richthofen (The Red Baron).
